Find Volatility in Github(official Github page):
https://github.com/volatilityfoundation/volatility
For Linux:
In Debian based distros(such as Ubuntu,Kali Linux,Mint and more) we use:
    $ sudo apt-get install volatility
For Mac OS:
    $ brew install volatility
For Windows:
    Install volatility.exe
     or install python2 and use 
     $ cd volatility
     $ python volatility.py
You can always use:
$ git clone https://github.com/volatilityfoundation/volatility.git
and install volatility via terminal
